<br>
I thought it was a good question, and to an extent, I think it still is.  However, over time I've let my own role-playing slip and slip to the point now where it is pretty much non-existant.  By and large, role-playing on this server was never outstanding or everpresent, but within a few months of the ruleset changes, role-playing disappeared outside from a few small, isolated pockets.<br>
<br>
It's pretty pointless trying to role-play when it's so misunderstood in this game, and there's so little good, real role-playing occuring around you.  Some people enjoy RPing by themselves, I personally don't.<br>
<br>
It's sort of a philosophical thing.  If only people who <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>intended</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to role-play, and knew how to role-play, or had an open mind about learning how to role-play came to play on this server, you would not have the same issues arising from  misunderstandings about role-playing, and people wouldn't be be absurdly accused of being racists in RL because a player on the role-playing preferred server doesn't understand the distinction between &quot;in character&quot; and &quot;out of character&quot; behavior.<br>
<br>
So you can see the issue a lot of role-players have.  Not only do most people seem to have no intention of role-playing, you even have a minority of people (seemingly about equal to the number of &quot;real&quot;, decent RPers) who are intolerant of RPing altogether.  That's pretty exasperating when there are dozens of other servers where a person can play if they don't want to RP or if RPing bothers them. <p>--Velsor<br>
